PRETORIA - Disgruntled Gauteng residents gathered outside the venue where Gauteng Premier David Makhura was delivering the State of the Province Address. Among them, were people who were affected by floods in Mamelodi late last year. READ: Mamelodi flood victim dies Another group demanding answers was Equal Education, which wants solutions to the high number of school deaths at Gauteng schools so far this year.
Mamelodi residents are still waiting for the land promised to them by Gauteng Premier David Makhura.